## 13. Application Commands

The application MUST expose two sub-commands, invoked as the first positional argument to `main.py`.

### 13.1 `start` — Initiate Instance Refresh

**Purpose:** Locates an ASG by tag, starts an instance refresh, and writes the `InstanceRefreshId` to `outputs/refresh.env`.

**Required arguments:**

| Argument | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `--tag-key` | string | The tag key used to locate the target ASG (e.g. `Name`, `Environment`) |
| `--tag-value` | string | The tag value to match against the specified key (e.g. `my-asg`, `production`) |

Both `--tag-key` and `--tag-value` MUST be provided together. Providing one without the other MUST result in an argument error.

**Optional arguments:**

| Argument | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--min-healthy-percentage` | integer | `90` | Minimum percentage of healthy instances during refresh |
| `--max-healthy-percentage` | integer | `100` | Maximum percentage of healthy instances during refresh, controlling the rate of new instance launch |
| `--instance-warmup` | integer | `300` | Warm-up time in seconds for new instances before they are considered healthy |
| `--no-skip-matching` | flag | `false` | If set, overrides the default behaviour and forces all instances to be replaced regardless of their current configuration (see Section 15) |
| `--checkpoint-percentages` | list of int | none | Optional list of percentages at which to pause the refresh |
| `--checkpoint-delay` | integer | `3600` | Seconds to wait at each checkpoint before continuing |

**Output:** On success the command MUST:

1. Write `INSTANCE_REFRESH_ID=<id>` to `outputs/refresh.env`
2. Log the refresh ID and ASG name to `stdout`

**Exit codes:**

| Code | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `0` | Refresh successfully initiated and artifact written |
| `1` | ASG not found or tag lookup returned no results |
| `2` | AWS API error |
| `3` | Invalid or missing arguments |
| `4` | Failed to write artifact file |

---

### 13.2 `monitor` — Monitor Refresh Completion

**Purpose:** Reads an `InstanceRefreshId` (from file or CLI), then polls the AWS API until the refresh reaches a terminal state or the timeout is exceeded.

**Required arguments:**

| Argument | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `--tag-key` | string | Tag key used to locate the target ASG |
| `--tag-value` | string | Tag value used to locate the target ASG |

**Optional arguments:**

| Argument | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--refresh-id` | string | read from `outputs/refresh.env` | The `InstanceRefreshId` to monitor. If not provided, read from the dotenv artifact |
| `--poll-interval` | integer | `30` | Seconds between each status poll |
| `--timeout` | integer | `1800` | Maximum seconds to wait before exiting with a timeout error |

**Terminal states:** The monitor command MUST exit when one of the following states is returned by the AWS API:

| AWS State | Exit Code | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `Successful` | `0` | Refresh completed successfully |
| `Failed` | `1` | Refresh failed |
| `Cancelled` | `2` | Refresh was cancelled |
| `RollbackSuccessful` | `4` | Refresh was rolled back successfully |
| `RollbackFailed` | `5` | Rollback attempt also failed |

**Local exit conditions:**

| Condition | Exit Code |
|---|---|
| Local timeout exceeded | `3` |
| Artifact file missing and no `--refresh-id` provided | `3` |
| AWS API error during polling | `2` |

**Behaviour:** On each poll the monitor MUST log the current status and `PercentageComplete`. On reaching a terminal state it MUST log a final summary including total elapsed time.

