## 14. Project Structure

The application MUST follow this structure:

```
project/
├── Dockerfile
├── .dockerignore
├── requirements.txt
├── config/
│   ├── config.yaml
│   └── config.example.yaml
└── src/
    ├── __init__.py
    ├── main.py
    └── modules/
        ├── __init__.py
        ├── asg_lookup.py      # ASG resolution via tag_key + tag_value
        ├── refresh_start.py   # start command logic and artifact writing
        └── refresh_monitor.py # monitor command logic and artifact reading
```

- Each directory containing Python modules MUST include an `__init__.py` file
- `main.py` MUST act solely as the entry point — parsing the sub-command and delegating to the appropriate module
- Business logic MUST reside in the relevant module, not in `main.py`
- Inter-module imports MUST use absolute package imports

---

## 15. Skip Matching

- `SkipMatching` MUST default to `true` in all `StartInstanceRefresh` API calls
- When `--no-skip-matching` is passed, the `SkipMatching` property MUST be set to `false`, forcing all instances to be replaced
- By default this means instances already running the desired launch template or configuration version are bypassed, reducing unnecessary replacement and refresh duration
- The use of `--no-skip-matching` MAY be used when a full replacement of all instances is required regardless of their current state, such as after a forced rollout
- The skip matching behaviour is governed entirely by the AWS API; the application MUST NOT attempt to replicate or override this logic client-side

---

## 16. ASG Name Lookup via Tags

- The application MUST resolve the target ASG exclusively via tag lookup using `--tag-key` and `--tag-value`; direct ASG name input MUST NOT be supported
- On startup, the application MUST call `DescribeAutoScalingGroups` and filter results client-side for ASGs whose tags contain the specified key=value pair
- If exactly one ASG matches, its name MUST be used for all subsequent API calls
- If zero ASGs match, the application MUST exit with code `1` and log a descriptive error message including the tag key and value searched
- If more than one ASG matches, the application MUST exit with code `1` and log the names of all matching ASGs, requiring the operator to use a more specific tag combination
- Tag matching MUST be case-sensitive

---

## 17. Max Healthy Percentage

- The `--max-healthy-percentage` argument controls the upper bound on healthy instance count during a refresh, expressed as a percentage of the ASG desired capacity
- Setting this above `100` permits AWS to launch replacement instances before terminating existing ones, enabling a faster refresh at the cost of temporarily running above desired capacity
- Setting this to `100` (the default) ensures the ASG never exceeds its desired capacity during the refresh
- The value MUST be an integer between `100` and `200` inclusive
- Values below `100` MUST be rejected with an argument error
- The value MUST be greater than or equal to `--min-healthy-percentage`; if it is not, the application MUST exit with code `3` before making any AWS API calls

---

## 18. Configuration Management

- Application defaults MUST be stored in `config/config.yaml`
- The configuration file MUST NOT contain AWS credentials or region; these MUST be injected at runtime
- The following keys MUST be supported in the config file:

```yaml
defaults:
  min_healthy_percentage: 90
  max_healthy_percentage: 100
  instance_warmup: 300
  poll_interval: 30
  timeout: 1800
  skip_matching: true  # default; set to false to force full instance replacement

artifacts:
  output_dir: outputs
  refresh_env_filename: refresh.env
```

- CLI arguments MUST take precedence over config file values
- The artifact output path (`output_dir` + `refresh_env_filename`) MUST be configurable via the config file but MUST default to `outputs/refresh.env`
- Configuration loading MUST fail fast with a clear error if the file is missing or malformed
- A `config.example.yaml` with all keys documented MUST be included in the repository

---

## 19. Compliance Checklist

Before publishing an image, the following MUST be verified:

- [ ] Base image pinned to Python 3.10+, non-`latest` tag
- [ ] All dependencies pinned to exact versions including `boto3` and `pyyaml`
- [ ] `PYTHONUNBUFFERED` and `PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE` set
- [ ] Non-root user defined and active
- [ ] No AWS credentials or secrets present in the image or config files
- [ ] `.dockerignore` present and complete
- [ ] Image tagged with a semantic version
- [ ] `ENTRYPOINT` defined; `CMD` defaults to `--help`
- [ ] `start` command accepts `--tag-key` and `--tag-value`; `--asg-name` is not present
- [ ] `start` command writes `INSTANCE_REFRESH_ID` to `outputs/refresh.env` in dotenv format
- [ ] `outputs/` directory created automatically if absent
- [ ] `--min-healthy-percentage` and `--max-healthy-percentage` implemented and validated against each other
- [ ] `--max-healthy-percentage` constrained to 100–200
- [ ] `SkipMatching` defaults to `true` in all StartInstanceRefresh calls
- [ ] `--no-skip-matching` flag correctly sets `SkipMatching` to `false`
- [ ] `monitor` command reads refresh ID from `outputs/refresh.env` when `--refresh-id` is not provided
- [ ] `monitor` command exits with correct code for each terminal state
- [ ] Poll interval and timeout implemented in `monitor`
- [ ] Tag lookup handles zero matches, one match, and multiple matches with appropriate exit codes
- [ ] Tag matching is case-sensitive
- [ ] IAM permissions documented; least privilege principle applied
- [ ] Example `.gitlab-ci.yml` included in repository documentation
